<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-12-02T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-12-02T18:00:00-05:00" n="106" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d106">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">500.A15A5/839: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Grew</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-12-02T18:00:00-05:00">December
                                    2, 1936—6 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>151. An instruction, No. 1141 of November 16, 1936, was sent to you with
                            regard to 14–16 inch guns. In view of publicity regarding new capital
                            ships here it has become most urgent for the Navy Department to have
                            this matter clarified at the earliest possible moment. Please,
                            therefore, telegraph your conclusions as soon as possible after receipt
                            of above-mentioned instruction so that the Department may determine the
                            course which should be followed. You should, however, take no action in
                            the matter pending the receipt of instructions.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Moore</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>